entity.name: Federal court hears Department of Justice's request to block Texas' controversial abortion ban
entity.description:
A federal judge in the US District Court for the Western District of Texas is hearing arguments from the US Department of Justice as well as the state of Texas on whether to block Texas Senate Bill 8, the ban on abortions past six weeks. The state law went into effect on September 1 and the Justice Department has said the law is "in open defiance of the Constitution," according to NBC News. 

The Justice Department sued Texas last month because the abortion ban violated the Supremacy Clause and equal protection under the 14th Amendment. The House also held a hearing on SB8 on Thursday, during which three female members of Congress testified about their decisions to have abortions.
